  "prompt": "I am graduating in may 2018, should I apply for CDS 1 of 2017?",
  "response": "If you are graduating in May 2018, it's important to consider the eligibility criteria and the timing of the Combined Defence Services (CDS) examination you are planning to apply for.\n\nCDS 1 of 2017 would have been conducted in February 2017, with notifications released in November 2016. Given that you will be graduating in May 2018, applying for CDS 1 of 2017 would not have been possible or relevant for you, as you would not have completed your graduation at the time of the exam or the subsequent SSB interviews.\n\nFor candidates graduating in May 2018, the appropriate cycle to consider would be CDS 2 of 2017 or CDS 1 of 2018, depending on the specific eligibility criteria at the time of application. Here's a general guideline:\n\n- **CDS 2 of 2017**: Notification would typically be released around August 2017, with the exam conducted in November 2017. You could apply for this if you were in your final year and expected to receive your degree by May 2018.\n- **CDS 1 of 2018**: Notification would typically be released around November 2017, with the exam conducted in February 2018. You could apply for this as well, given your graduation timeline.\n\nAlways check the latest eligibility criteria and notification details on the official UPSC website before applying. The key is to ensure that you will have your degree certificate or provisional certificate by the time you join the training academy, which is typically several months after the written exam and SSB interview.\n\nGiven the timeline you've mentioned, you should have been looking at applying for CDS exams that align with your graduation timeline, such as CDS 2 of 2017 or CDS 1 of 2018.",
